div.p:
These [are] the basic quotas for the life of the agreement but have been
                        adjusted by increases or decreases for the year 1937–38 resulting in the
                        following changed figures: Belgium 15,000 tons; Czechoslovakia 340,000;
                        Germany 50,000; Hungary 20,000; Poland 100,000; Soviet Union 218,500;
                        reserve for countries like France and Yugoslavia 25,000. Total net quota for
                        1937–38 3,611,000 tons.
